<i>Lumos Maxima.</i>

2
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:41,709
<i>Lumos Maxima.</i>

3
00:01:01,812 --> 00:01:03,439
<i>Lumos Maxima.</i>

4
00:01:05,691 --> 00:01:07,610
<i>Lumos Maxima.</i>

5
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,489
<i>Lumos Maxima!</i>

6
00:01:41,394 --> 00:01:42,478
Harry. Harry.

7
00:01:42,645 --> 00:01:44,647
Harry, open the door.

8
00:01:46,524 --> 00:01:48,359
Uh...

9
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:52,613
Marge. How lovely to see--

10
00:01:54,073 --> 00:01:57,451
Uncle Vernon,
I need you to sign this form.

11
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:58,953
What is it?

12
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:01,247
Nothing. School stuff.

13
00:02:01,414 --> 00:02:04,083
Later perhaps, if you behave.

14
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:06,460
I will if she does.

15
00:02:06,627 --> 00:02:09,755
- Oh, you're still here, are you?
- Yes.

16
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,800
Don't say yes
in that ungrateful way.

17
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:14,927
Damn good of my brother
to keep you.

18
00:02:15,094 --> 00:02:18,472
He'd have been straight to an orphanage
if he'd been dumped on my doorstep.

19
00:02:19,849 --> 00:02:23,978
Is that my Dudders?
Is that my little neffy-pooh?

20
00:02:24,145 --> 00:02:25,938
Give us a kiss. Come on. Up, up.

21
00:02:26,105 --> 00:02:28,399
Take Marge's suitcase upstairs.

22
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:30,526
Okay.

23
00:02:33,904 --> 00:02:36,782
Finish that off for Mommy.
Good boy, Rippy-pooh.

24
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:40,745
- Can I tempt you, Marge?
- Just a small one.

25
00:02:40,953 --> 00:02:43,914
Excellent nosh, Petunia.

26
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:46,500
A bit more.

27
00:02:47,043 --> 00:02:50,338
Usually just a fry-up for me,
what with 12 dogs.

28
00:02:50,546 --> 00:02:53,132
Just a bit more. That's a boy.

29
00:02:55,593 --> 00:02:58,220
Ah! You wanna try
a little drop of brandy?

30
00:02:58,387 --> 00:03:02,433
A little drop of brandy-brandy
windy-wandy for Rippy-pippy-pooh?

31
00:03:03,934 --> 00:03:05,728
What are you smirking at?

32
00:03:05,895 --> 00:03:07,730
Where did you send the boy,
Vernon?

33
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:11,233
St. Brutus'. It's a fine institution
for hopeless cases.

34
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:14,403
Do they use a cane
at St. Brutus', boy?

35
00:03:17,865 --> 00:03:19,200
Oh, yeah.

36
00:03:19,408 --> 00:03:22,078
Yeah. I've been beaten loads of times.

37
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:24,830
Excellent. I won't have this
namby-pamby...

38
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:28,167
...wishy-washy nonsense about
not beating people who deserve it.

39
00:03:28,334 --> 00:03:31,462
You mustn't blame yourself
about how this one turned out.

40
00:03:31,629 --> 00:03:35,549
It's all to do with blood.
Bad blood will out.

41
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:37,885
What is it the boy's father did,
Petunia?

42
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:41,055
Nothing. He didn't work.
He was unemployed.

43
00:03:41,222 --> 00:03:44,058
- And a drunk too, no doubt?
- That's a lie.

44
00:03:44,225 --> 00:03:46,769
- What did you say?
- My dad wasn't a drunk.

45
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:53,859
Don't worry. Don't fuss, Petunia.
I have a very firm grip.

46
00:03:54,026 --> 00:03:55,861
I think it's time you went to bed.

47
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:59,281
Quiet, Vernon. You, clean it up.

48
00:04:00,658 --> 00:04:03,661
Actually, it's nothing to do
with the father.

49
00:04:03,869 --> 00:04:07,623
It's all to do with the mother.
You see it all the time with dogs.

50
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:11,836
If something's wrong with the bitch,
then something's wrong with the pup.

51
00:04:12,044 --> 00:04:13,712
Shut up! Shut up!

52
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:22,763
Right. Let me tell you...

53
00:04:36,152 --> 00:04:38,112
Oh...

54
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:46,328
Vernon!

55
00:04:49,373 --> 00:04:51,167
Vernon! Vernon, do something!

56
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:56,881
Ow! Ripper! Ow...

57
00:05:34,627 --> 00:05:36,629
Stop!

58
00:05:39,215 --> 00:05:41,759
I've got you, Marge. I've got you.

59
00:05:45,221 --> 00:05:47,181
- Hold on, hold on.
- Get off.

60
00:05:48,474 --> 00:05:50,267
- Don't you dare!
- Sorry.

61
00:05:51,477 --> 00:05:53,312
Oh, Vernon.

62
00:05:53,479 --> 00:05:55,231
Oh, God.

63
00:05:55,397 --> 00:05:57,191
Marge!

64
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,450
Please!

65
00:06:07,076 --> 00:06:09,286
Marge!

66
00:06:10,371 --> 00:06:13,541
Come back!

67
00:06:37,523 --> 00:06:39,942
You bring her back!
You bring her back now.

68
00:06:40,109 --> 00:06:42,528
- You put her right!
- No. She deserved what she got.

69
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:46,949
- Keep away from me.
- You can't do magic outside school.

70
00:06:47,157 --> 00:06:50,160
- Yeah? Try me.
- They won't let you back now.

71
00:06:50,327 --> 00:06:51,662
You've nowhere to go.

72
00:06:51,829 --> 00:06:54,164
I don't care.
Anywhere is better than here.

73
00:06:54,164 --> 00:07:24,164
